### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python application file.
- Implements the web server, routing, and all business logic.
- Handles reading from and writing to local text files in the 'data' directory.
- Manages data parsing, searching, filtering, and playlist management.
- Serves the HTML templates with dynamic data.

data/
- Contains all the local text files storing the application's data as specified.
- songs.txt, artists.txt, albums.txt, genres.txt, playlists.txt, playlist_songs.txt.

templates/
- Contains all HTML template files for the 10 pages defined in the requirements.
- Each HTML file corresponds to a page (e.g., dashboard.html for Dashboard Page).
- Templates include placeholders for dynamic content populated by app.py.

static/
- Contains static assets used by the web application.
- css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
- js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).
- images/: Folder for storing cover art, artist photos, and album covers referenced in the UI.

This structure keeps the backend logic consolidated in a single Python file (app.py) for simplicity, while separating frontend templates and static assets for maintainability and clarity. The data directory holds all persistent data in text files as required.
